# Ephemeral Playwright auth-fixture artifacts (debug runs)
/prod-*-state.png

# Ephemeral runtime evidence — D.1 standalone spec captures these on every
# `playwright test` run (per `tests/screenshots/user-stories/US-STAB-D1/
# evidence.md` lines 187-192: "captured at E2E + visual run-time, NOT
# committed at this implementation step"). evidence.md remains tracked.
tests/screenshots/user-stories/US-STAB-D1/*.png

# Playwright evidence captures (FU-E13-EVIDENCE-PNG-IDEMPOTENCY) — written
# unconditionally via page.screenshot({path:...}) on every `playwright test`
# run. Bytes differ between runs due to anti-aliasing / font-rendering /
# frame-timing variance, dirtying the working tree on every run. These are
# observational records (one per AC step) of how the UI looked when the
# spec executed, NOT test assertions — the assertions are the
# expect(...) calls in the specs themselves. Regenerable by re-running the
# suite locally. evidence.md narratives remain TRACKED.
#
# NOT ignored: tests/screenshots/audit-2026-*/  (one-shot historical
# manual-audit captures; no spec auto-overwrites them).
# NOT ignored: tests/**/*-snapshots/  +  tests/**/__snapshots__/  (Playwright
# toHaveScreenshot() + Vitest snapshot baselines — these ARE test assertions
# and must stay tracked).
tests/screenshots/user-stories/US-*/**/*.png
tests/screenshots/reduced-motion/*.png
tests/screenshots/smoke/**/*.png

# Supabase CLI local link state (machine-specific; should not be committed)
supabase/.temp/linked-project.json

# Mockup screenshots (regenerable from HTML)
Design/mockups-brainstorm/*/screenshot.png

